response_value: Well, I think that the 'b' and 'p' sounds are made in the same location ( I forget where, but I know they have a very similar origin), so I think the experiment was about how people distinguish that difference in isolation, without the context of a sentence.

I think overall, I tried to focus on the end sound of the word as much as possible, but it was pretty hard. At times I would hear the world "laugh" and associate it with "lap" because it sounds more like "lap" than "lab" to me. There was also a part where the options were dog barking or cat meowing, but the animal sounded like a dog whining or something, so I just went back and forth on that sound.
